Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Cut @broccoli florets{8%oz}
into bite-size pieces, if necessary. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2},
separating whites from greens. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, half the ginger, 3/4 cup water,
and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer.
Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to
serve.

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}. Season
generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until golden brown and
tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Meanwhile, place @sesame seeds{1%tbsp} in a large,
dry #pan{} over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring, until golden brown and fragrant,
~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat. Transfer to a #small bowl{}; season with salt and
pepper. Wash out pan.

Pat @salmon{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season generously with salt and
pepper. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in pan used for sesame seeds over
medium-high heat. Add salmon skin sides down; cook until skin is crisp,
~{5-7%minutes}. Flip and cook until fish is cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.
Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium heat. Add scallion whites and remaining
ginger; cook until ginger is fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @seafood stock
concentrate{1}, juice from half the lime, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and 1/4 cup water.
Cook until slightly reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from heat and stir in
@butter{2%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp}, lime zest, and half the scallion
greens. Season with salt and pepper. Divide rice, broccoli, and salmon
between plates. Top salmon with sauce and broccoli with as many sesame seeds as
you like. Garnish with remaining scallion greens. Serve with remaining lime
wedges on the side.

> We know you'll REELY love this one.